    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Lilian Whiting (1847-1942) was an American writer, editor, activist and journalist.  Born in Niagara Falls, N. Y. , Whiting is best known for being one of the first women to edit a newspaper, and for writing the first biography of Kate Field.   Her newspaper credits include literary editor of <emph render="italic">The Boston Traveler</emph> and editor in chief of <emph render="italic">The Boston Budget.</emph>  She was also active in the cause of women's suffrage.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Lilian Whiting Papers </emph> consists of correspondence and a three-page holograph poem. </p>
    </scopecontent>
